FBIS3-53033 "drnes007_r_94003" FBIS-NES-94-007 Document Type:Daily Report 11 Jan 1994 India Rao Urges Ties With Beijing To Ensure Peace BK1001163694 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 1530 GMT 10 Jan 94 BK1001163694 Delhi All India Radio Network Language: English Article Type:BFN [Excerpt] The prime minister says that in the changed international situation, India and China have a bigger role to play to ensure peace and stability. Speaking to a delegation of the Chinese Communist Party which called on him in New Delhi today, Mr. Narasimha Rao expressed satisfaction over the steady growth of bilateral relations. The prime minister also extended an invitation to the Chinese president to visit later this year. The delegation is led by Mr. Wen Jiabao, member of the Secretariat of the Central Committee of the Chinese Communist Party. According to the Congress-I spokesman, Mr. Chandulal Chandrakar, the delegation called for greater cooperation between India and China in agriculture, science and technology, rural development, industry and culture. It also emphasized the need for more interaction between the Congress-I and the Chinese Communist Party. The delegation earlier called on the home minister, Mr. S.B. Chavan. The minister reiterated the government's commitment to maintain friendly relations with China and peace and tranquillity along the border. [passage omitted]
